modules.description: This module creates commit metadata with author, timestamp, and message for version-controlled stores. It operates on commit info structures compatible with Git, using MirageOS-compatible time and authoring data. Useful for generating precise commit history entries during repository synchronization or logging events in a distributed store.

This module generates commit metadata for version-controlled stores, capturing author, timestamp, and message in structures compatible with Git. It supports precise tracking of changes during synchronization or logging in distributed environments. Operations include creating and manipulating commit info entries using MirageOS-compatible time and author data. Example usage includes recording structured commit history during repository updates or audit logging in a distributed store.
